CGI Windows and Doors appoints Brian Covey as Director of Sales

Media Contact:
Kim Drew, APR
706.568.9504
kimdrewpr@bellsouth.net
To read official release, please visit: http://www.prweb.com/releases/2016/03/prweb13272916.htm
CGI Windows & Doors, a subsidiary of PGT, Inc. (NASDAQ: PGTI), the nation’s leading manufacturer and supplier of impact-resistant windows and doors, is pleased to announce the addition of Brian Covey to CGI’s senior management team. Effectively immediately, Covey will serve as the Director of Sales and oversee all aspects of sales, business development and project estimating.
“Brian is a natural fit for this role given his proven leadership skills, sales expertise, and understanding of our customers, employees and products,” said Jeff Jackson, President and Chief Operating Office, PGTI. “We’re excited to have him in this new role as we expand our CGI sales team and further strengthen our customer relationships.”
Covey previously served as Regional Sales Manager for PGT Custom Windows & Doors in the Southeast, Florida region from 2012-2016. Before joining PGT, he served as an Area Sales Manager for Masco Cabinetry.
“Bringing Brian on board was an easy decision.” said Steven E. Dawson, Vice President and General Manager of CGI. “He has over 20 years of experience in building products and already has strong relationships in the market. We are thrilled to have Brian join our team”.
ABOUT CGI:
CGI was established in 1992 and has consistently built a reputation based on designing and manufacturing quality impact-resistant products that meet or exceed the stringent Miami-Dade County impact standards. The Company has over 300 employees at its manufacturing plant in Miami, Florida. Today the Company continues to lead as an innovator in product craftsmanship, strength and style, and its brands are highly recognized and respected by the architectural community. CGI product lines include the Estate Collection, Sentinel by CGI, Estate Entrances, Commercial Series, and Targa by CGI. CGI Windows and Doors is a wholly owned subsidiary of PGT, Inc. (NASDAQ: PGTI). For additional information, visit cgiwindows.com.
 
 


Innovation and Progress: Product Updates from CGI Windows & Doors

Media Contact:
Kim Drew, APR
706.568.9504
kimdrewpr@bellsouth.net
To read official release, please visit: http://www.prweb.com/releases/2016/02/prweb13216795.htm
Miami, Florida (PRWEB) February 16, 2016
As the premier manufacturer of hurricane impact-resistant windows and doors, products from CGI Windows & Doors are manufactured to the most exacting industry standards for both new and existing construction. To achieve and maintain this exceptional level of high-performance, high-aesthetic product, customer needs are evaluated on a regular basis, leading to timely product updates, such as the following:
Sentinel by CGI:
The Sentinel by CGI line is known for exceptional craftsmanship, energy efficiency, and durability at an affordable price. Each door and window is custom manufactured to enhance the aesthetics of any home style while delivering protection from the most extreme coastal weather conditions. What’s new:

    Sentinel by CGI now offered in Class 1 Clear Anodized; and
    Sentinel Series 150 Sliding Glass Door now with a new, squared-off handle option.

Estate Collection:
Recognized by architects as a premier line of hurricane impact windows, the Estate Collection offers a best-in-class performance against hurricane force damage. Hand-crafted details and superior engineering are why this line can be found in elegant homes, prestigious resorts, hotels, schools, and office buildings. What’s new:

    360/375 Anodized products will now come with a smooth, stylish gray hardware finish.

ABOUT CGI:
CGI was established in 1992 and has consistently built a reputation based on designing and manufacturing quality impact-resistant products that meet or exceed the stringent Miami-Dade County impact standards. The Company has over 300 employees at its manufacturing plant in Miami, Florida. Today the Company continues to lead as an innovator in product craftsmanship, strength and style, and its brands are highly recognized and respected by the architectural community. CGI product lines include the Estate Collection, Sentinel by CGI, Estate Entrances, Commercial Series, and Targa by CGI. CGI Windows and Doors is a wholly owned subsidiary of PGT, Inc. (NASDAQ: PGTI). For additional information, visit cgiwindows.com.
 
 


CGI Windows & Doors Rewards FIU Students Who Walk on Water

Media Contact:
Kim Drew, APR
706.568.9504
kimdrewpr@bellsouth.net
To read official release, please visit: http://www.prweb.com/releases/2015/12/prweb13130164.htm
Florida International University students in the Materials & Methods of Construction Class taught by FIU Architecture Professor Jaime Canaves were issued a challenge by their teacher: Successfully construct shoes that will allow the student to walk across a campus lake – with minimum water contact. CGI Windows & Doors offered a $1,000 scholarship to the 2015 “Walk on Water” winner, supporting the program for the second year in a row.
“We were once again astounded by the creative genius shown by these students,” said Steven E. Dawson, vice president and general manager of CGI Windows & Doors. “It’s our job as members of the architectural community to do all we can to encourage their ingenuity and professional growth. It’s an honor to be part of the “Walk on Water” program for the second year.”  
“CGI’s generous support of our students is most appreciated,” said Brian Schriner, Dean of the College of Architecture + The Arts at FIU. “This is yet another example of this company’s commitment to our community and its success.”
A 25+-year tradition for the FIU Modesto A. Maidique Campus, all students who successfully walked across Green Lake received an A in the class. The 2015 competition featured 50 students, with Daniel Tabet completing the walk first and claiming the CGI Windows & Doors scholarship.
The $1,000 winning scholarship is part of a $5,000 total scholarship amount donated by CGI Windows & Doors to the FIU Department of Architecture throughout the school year. Also included: $750 and $500 amounts awarded to the second- and third-place “Walk on Water” finishers, respectively; and $2,750 for other scholarships during the spring semester.
ABOUT CGI:
CGI was established in 1992 and has consistently built a reputation based on designing and manufacturing quality impact-resistant products that meet or exceed the stringent Miami-Dade County impact standards. The Company has over 300 employees at its manufacturing plant in Miami, Florida. Today the Company continues to lead as an innovator in product craftsmanship, strength and style, and its brands are highly recognized and respected by the architectural community. CGI product lines include the Estate Collection, Sentinel by CGI, Estate Entrances, Commercial Series, and Targa by CGI. CGI Windows and Doors is a wholly owned subsidiary of PGT, Inc. (NASDAQ: PGTI). For additional information, visit cgiwindows.com.
ABOUT THE FIU DEPARTMENT OF ARCHITECTURE:
The FIU Department of Architecture trains students in the profession of architecture to become thoughtful practitioners, critical thinkers, and broad visionaries with the skills and knowledge to enhance their communities and the built environment around them. The Department has a world-class faculty engaged in architectural practice and research on issues of design, sustainability, history/theory/criticism, sea-level rise, digital fabrication, and a whole host of interdisciplinary areas that advance knowledge in South Florida and across the globe. For more information, go to architecture.fiu.edu.
 


CGI Windows & Doors Names Frank Perna as Director of Operations

Media Contact:
Kim Drew, APR
706.568.9504
kimdrewpr@bellsouth.net
to read official release, please visit: http://www.prweb.com/releases/Perna/Ops/prweb13028031.htm
Miami, FL (PRWEB) October 20, 2015
CGI Windows & Doors is pleased to announce the hiring of Frank Perna as director of operations for the Miami-based manufacturer of hurricane windows and doors. Perna joined CGI in September 2015.
“Frank is an excellent addition to the CGI management team,” said Steven E. Dawson, vice president and general manager of CGI Windows & Doors. “The depth of his experience – 25 years in the fenestration industry – is incredible; we look forward to benefitting from his extensive knowledge and experience.”
In his new capacity, Perna oversees all aspects of manufacturing, shipping, purchasing, quality control, and logistics.
When asked what appealed to him about CGI Windows & Doors, Perna’s reply was quick: “The company’s strong foundation and fast growth. Being owned by a larger company equals resources for smart growth; I’m excited to work together with a team of such open, talented, people to continue moving CGI forward.”
Prior to joining CGI, Perna worked as vice president of operations at several window companies located throughout the country.
